The paper deals with question answering for privacy policies, which involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques (related to cs.CL and cs.AI). It also involves legal perspectives, as privacy policies have legal implications (related to cs.CY and cs.CR). Finally, the paper presents a challenging corpus for question answering, which could be of interest to researchers working on machine learning and natural language processing (related to cs.LG).
